criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. have been diagnosed with stage I, II, or III breast cancer;

          2. are female breast cancer patients over the age of 18;

          3. have completed anti-cancer treatment via surgery and/or chemotherapy and /or radiation
             therapy at the McGill University Health Centre Breast Clinic;

          4. are fluent in written and spoken English or French;

          5. are alert and oriented and capable of giving informed consent;

          6. have an Internet connection at home that supports participation in coaching sessions
             via videoconferencing (zoom).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. have a recurrence of breast cancer;

          2. are diagnosed with a second cancer;

          3. are diagnosed with stage IV breast cancer due to their worse prognosis; and 4) have an
             active psychiatric diagnosis that would render adherence to the study problematic.
